<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-3744] The precision should be 17 (16 bits need after dot) after dot for double type.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-3744</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The precision is lost when converting double to string.&lt;br/&gt;
E.g:&lt;br/&gt;
double PI = 3.1415926535897931;&lt;br/&gt;
string value = format(&quot;%.16g&quot;, PI);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The value will be &apos;3.141592653589793&apos; and last 1 is lost after format operation.&lt;br/&gt;
But expected value should be &apos;3.1415926535897931&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Solution:&lt;br/&gt;
string value = format(&quot;%.17g&quot;, PI);&lt;/p&gt;</description>
